        <div id="approach" class="page">
          <div class="description">
            <p> Our work is driven by meaning, honesty and high quality. We take
              pride in delivering made-to-measure projects that are always
              based on understanding the big picture. </p>
          </div>
          <div class="content">
            <div class="design">
              <h4>Design Thinking + Doing</h4>
              <p> In our work, we don’t rely on any certain dogma but instead
                use our experience to pick the tried and tested methodologies
                in both intangible and tangible phases of our projects.
                Let's get to work. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="behaviour">
              <h4>Behaviour First</h4>
              <p> The core of our work is figuring how people behave and how
                they perceive the world around them. From these insights we
                design interactions which form the foundation in the
                relationship between the consumer and your product. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="context">
              <h4>Systems Thinking</h4>
              <p> We always design for the next, larger context in mind.
                The holistic system view enables us to better understand
                the effect of our work — be it economic, social or sustainable. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="interaction">
              <h4>Design Verbs, not Nouns</h4>
              <p> Interactions don’t exist in a vacuum but instead belong to a
                larger system. Before deciding what to build, it is important
                to first ask the right questions. This enables us to architect
                a system of solutions on different fidelities. Instead of
                designing a chair, first find the reasons why people sit. </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
